new features: -added new input source for socket connection via USB Tethering to our Raspberry Pi (named TcpIoService) -changed web layout to a simplistic black and white look - like a sheet of paper with tables on it (menu structure is still similar) -added web page with live information (flying pilot, fastest time, current flight time, estimated flight time and more) -added web page with start list -added web page with overall results in one table -incorporated wind sensor data -show in Titlebar and on live web page in a userfriendly format -speech notification when wind speed or direction is illegal regarding the FAI rules -usage and parameters are configurable in settings dialog -import all pilots and race configuration data (predefined start list with groups and rounds, ...) from/to csv file -added FilteredFilePickerActivity to only see compatible files (*.json and *.csv) on import -show current IP in settings for accessing the results server -show group in results dialogs -added functionality for hardware button triggering "score current flight zero and interrupt the automatic to start the next pilot afterwards" -added functionality for hardware button awarding penalties (accompanied by new beep sound) -added finish Race button in next round dialog -added button for rotate shuffle to the add pilots dialog -automatically accept flight time of a finished flight automatically after 5 seconds of inactivity and move on to the next pilot -added com.amitshekhar.android:debug-db:1.0.1 for database debugging at runtime (adds readout/editing on a web page through a dedicated socket connection) -added start_pos and group_nr and points to racetimes database table to simplify internal start order handling/changing and group handling for pilots and web results displaying
bugfixes: -don't overwrite volume setting (with to maximum), so that it can be adjusted to the preferred setting by the user -setting voice synthesis options in settings dialog didn't work correctly and caused crashes when set from within race -added a country code definition json file to be able to derive the [default/initial] TTS language from the Locale -on/off course not displayed in RaceTimerFrag4 on late entry -use SoundPool instead of mediaplayer to decrease buzzer sound latency -fixed NullPointerException in RaceActivity List rendering -limit RaceResultsServer socket connections and set MIN_PRIOTRITY to prevent overload and disturbance of RaceTimerActivity -customized some german translations -fixed race start_number and offset processing
